I indeed do write, right?) =================== 495/496 Surabaya, June 14, 1897 Dear wife and children, you have certainly already heard long, my dear, it again so bad looks sad with the trip and chartering. Waited a long time, many difficulties of traveling and now additionally freight to America with little freight, nothing earn and again a very long separation from the only ones who love us. Yes, my dear, sad, but possibly still an order of providence. ---- Now that the boys are two years older again before I see them and what can I do for their leadership and how little had joy we have actually. No, I\'ll not complain, I believe those days that we\'ve been together, also have double, even triple delight delivered. But now we see each other this trip again. America will take care of that offer no opportunity.If there would be a time ever come when we can stay together? s-rf. f I fl / l C \\ I 1 7 \'\\ 1 lt\' o. J.,. Jo a IV) Thou hast certainly received the portraits. Do you find they are not similar right? The helmsman not lucky this trip also to have to go, at least if he stays aboard to America. I doubt it though. Because our office seems not a promotion for mates to be, and I think he does for another opportunity will look like. Health is good, I\'m totally fine. With mates and pupils also going well. Versluis wanted to be placed at the Martina, but now we are chartered, it changed course again, it was to learn and lie still with Oostenburg not teach the boys of course much. Was our chartering now through to Falmouth, it was better for the boys but I could also as vd Low bet last year, his wife then bring to America. But dear dear wife, it will not go now. Not only the cost but additionally stay, and lastnotleast winter over the Atlantic Ocean. No female, on this difficult passage I dare you not at wintertime. It would do too much harm your health. If I can I will this week send a little money, how much I do not know yet. H. Scboo this week I received a letter