-------177 ','have been on board years now have to sail at their own expense or at least have to pay this. later Now dear John I\'m no longer news. Van der Laag\'m writing to his wife, and says nothing to know more, but believe Jansen celebrates birthday present. Now wijfke love you, consoling let the boys do well even write me. Be intimately geomhelsd and kissed the guys through you so dearly loving husband HlBron PS Greeting mother and Lina. -------------------------------------- Bladzij 497/500 497 is white and the pages 498 t / m 500 are missing. =================== Finally. From other sources it is known that the Oostenburg had flirted with an English ship and heavy damage. Collision in 1898 The English ship sank, no one drowned. The crew of the Oostenburg each received a medal and two pounds. The captain got a silver laber. All this according Okko Bron, who had a second book with letters in his possession. The boat was sold to Norway in 1898 and Grandpa bought Appingedam the stronghold a drugstore. In 1917, the Oostenburg disappeared without a trace at sea. Personally, I doubt whether the reward is sometimes mentioned relates to the rescue of the crew of the Eastem Monarch. Maybe there is sometimes a second part \"Private Bron\" with more clarity. Heemskerk, born in 2005 Ben Lyon, 14-7-1932 son of Marten HJBron .-; 3 Y LIJ -l !! f ;; 3 · 177 --------------------------------------','1');
